         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... || In the V.-tune: || Should he (enjoy) a poisonous dish as good (food) ... who loves [his] life, why</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>20-21</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... or why should one be fond of (?) a stained ... (how should) someone who wants to live, (yearn for [the smell of] a nice-smelling blue) lotus containing a snake</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... How should I love kingship, oppressing me with the royal ...  1. And also, father, how could someone who [is] knowledgeable in it,</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wie sollte ich die Königswürde lieben, die mich bedrückt durch die königlichen ... ?</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">How should I love the rank of king, which oppresses me with royal ... ?</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>169</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... or desirous be? See, oh lord: || In the P.-tune: || Hostilities [and] ...  ... [are] also royal obligations</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>311</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... of the kings [for] many years. (And) evil [is] the obligation, to the one [who is] ... (by) hate confused, at the (time) of [his] death.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>45</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>104</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... When he had heard this, (the king says) in bewilderment: ... (Oh lord,) my son! [For] years you (have (?))</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>247</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... This you have not actually seen ... ... with regard to being a ruler (?) as a teacher</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>247</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (This) you have (not really) seen. This you do (not) know. ... ... kingship is (not) of such kind. Excitedly</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>129</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(the prince says to the king:) Oh lord, in the doing of the kings (I do not see) the true knowledge of it [i.e. kingship]. ... The king says: Speak, speak, [my] son! (In) what</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>272f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>224</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(way) do you really know the doing (of kings)? The prince says: Listen, father! Just like a human clearly seeing (one’s) ... shoulders without a callus</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (just so,) having the memory of the births, I remember [my] (previous) births. || In the Y.-  tune: || (In) earlier births I have </seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (genau so) erinnere ich mich, da ich die Erinnerung an die Geburten habe, der (früheren) Geburten.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... (just so), since I have memory of the incarnations, I remember [my?] (previous) births.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>375</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>715</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>375</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... resorted (to cruelty) in order to preserve the realms. A man (made) a mistake, ... certainly the (command (?)) to kill</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">The translation is largely based on <bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>20-21</citedRange></bibl>, and <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/></bibl>. It is given for both fragments (A 83 and A 76) together here, separated by a slash (<hi>/</hi>).</note><note type="remarks">A 76 (right hand side) and A 83 (middle part) belong to the same leaf, but do not immediately connect to each other.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">This tune has 4x18 syllables, rhythm 7/7/4.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">This tune has 4x14 syllables, rhythm 7/7.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="lingcomment"><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1954b"/><citedRange>260</citedRange></bibl> has <hi>(e)sneṃ</hi> as adjective (“shoulder-”).</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">This tune (<hi>Yaśo(dha)ravilāpaṃ</hi>) has 4x18 syllables, rhythm 7/7/4.</note></p>
